  <title>Working with Tracks</title>

  <p>Tracks are the building blocks of your project. Each track contains 
  a single audio recording.</p>

  <section id="add-track">
    <title>Adding a Track</title>
    <p>To add a new track:</p>
    <list>
      <item><p>Click the <gui style="button">+</gui> button in the header bar, or</p></item>
      <item><p>Press <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>T</key></keyseq></p></item>
    </list>
    <p>New tracks are automatically named "Track 1", "Track 2", and so on.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="rename-track">
    <title>Renaming a Track</title>
    <steps>
      <item><p>Click the <gui style="button">âœï¸</gui> (edit) button on the left side of the track.</p></item>
      <item><p>Enter the new name in the dialog.</p></item>
      <item><p>Click <gui style="button">Rename</gui> or press <key>Enter</key>.</p></item>
    </steps>
    <note style="tip">
      <p>Give tracks descriptive names like "Vocals", "Guitar", or "Interview" 
      to keep your project organized.</p>
    </note>
  </section>

  <section id="delete-track">
    <title>Deleting a Track</title>
    <p>To delete a track, click the <gui style="button">ğŸ—‘ï¸</gui> (delete) button 
    on the right side of the track.</p>
    <note style="warning">
      <p>Deleting a track permanently removes its recording. This action cannot be undone.</p>
    </note>
  </section>

  <section id="mute-track">
    <title>Muting a Track</title>
    <p>Muting allows you to silence a track during playback while keeping it in the project:</p>
    <list>
      <item><p>Click the <gui style="button">ğŸ”Š</gui> (speaker) button to mute the track.</p></item>
      <item><p>The icon changes to <gui style="button">ğŸ”‡</gui> when muted.</p></item>
      <item><p>Click again to unmute.</p></item>
    </list>
    <p>Muted tracks still "play" (their position advances), but produce no audio output. 
    This is useful for isolating certain tracks while reviewing your mix.</p>
  </section>

